## Component Priority (MUST FOLLOW)

When building UI, follow this priority order:

### 1. Use Ariane Components First (Preferred)
Always check if an Ariane component exists before creating custom elements.

\`\`\`jsx
// ✅ GOOD - Use Ariane components
import { Text, Heading, CTAButton, Flex, Box } from '@framework/components/ariane';

<Flex gap="MD" alignItems="center">
  <Heading level={2}>Title</Heading>
  <Text type="caption" color="default.main.secondary">Subtitle</Text>
  <CTAButton emphasis="primary">Click me</CTAButton>
</Flex>
\`\`\`

\`\`\`jsx
// ❌ BAD - Creating custom elements when Ariane components exist
<div className="flex gap-4 items-center">
  <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold">Title</h2>
  <p className="text-sm text-gray-500">Subtitle</p>
  <button className="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Click me</button>
</div>
\`\`\`

### 2. Extend with Tailwind Classes (When Needed)
If Ariane components need minor adjustments, use the \`className\` prop with Tailwind:

\`\`\`jsx
// ✅ GOOD - Ariane component with Tailwind overrides
<Box className="mt-8 border-t border-neutral-200">
  <Text type="lead" className="italic">Custom styled text</Text>
</Box>
\`\`\`

### 3. Create Custom Components (Last Resort)
Only create new components when:
- No suitable Ariane component exists
- User explicitly requests a custom component
- The UI pattern is unique to this prototype

