## ScrollContainer Usage

**Always use \`ScrollContainer\` when content needs to scroll.** It provides minimal, elegant scrollbars that appear only on hover.

### Basic Usage

\`\`\`jsx
import { ScrollContainer } from '@framework/components/ariane';

// Fixed height container
<ScrollContainer className="h-[400px]">
  <div>Long scrollable content...</div>
</ScrollContainer>
\`\`\`

### In Flex Layouts

\`\`\`jsx
// ScrollContainer fills remaining space in a flex column
<Flex flexDirection="column" className="h-full">
  <Heading level={2}>Fixed Header</Heading>
  <ScrollContainer className="flex-1">
    <div>Scrollable content that fills remaining space</div>
  </ScrollContainer>
</Flex>
\`\`\`

### Horizontal Scrolling

\`\`\`jsx
<ScrollContainer horizontal className="max-w-full">
  <Flex gap="MD" className="w-max">
    {items.map(item => <Card key={item.id} />)}
  </Flex>
</ScrollContainer>
\`\`\`

### With Lists

\`\`\`jsx
<ScrollContainer className="h-[300px]">
  <Flex flexDirection="column" gap="SM">
    {users.map(user => (
      <UserCard key={user.id} user={user} />
    ))}
  </Flex>
</ScrollContainer>
\`\`\`

### Important Notes

- **Always set a height** using \`className\` (e.g., \`h-[400px]\`, \`h-full\`, \`flex-1\`)
- Use \`horizontal\` prop for horizontal scrolling
- The \`ref\` prop provides access to the SimpleBar instance for programmatic scrolling

